  <li id="comment-29832" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/07/you-dont-forget/#comment-29832"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-07-18T04:25:54-04:00">Monday, July 18, 2011 at 4:25 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Annie, I wish I had an answer for you about the sugar content and suitability for canning, but I don&#39;t know enough about canning to confidently say one way or the other.  I wonder if <a href="http://www.uga.edu/nchfp/publications/publications_usda.html" rel="nofollow">this publication</a> might help?</p>
    </div>

