    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Oh! I&#39;ve made this before, but it was &#8220;Japanese&#8221; jam&#8230; people making homemade jam but without the proper equipment.<br />It used one-third the weight of sugar to the fruit and no lemon rind, but is more or less the same- maceration, gentle cooking.<br />I too am not a jam fan but I love this kind of jam!<br />I want to try it with the lemon zest like here now.<br />(p.s the recipe I used suggested that you can also use plums, plumcotes, apricots etc. I tried apricot and bay, wonderful.)</p>
