    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/08082461658054093889" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">desertplantlady</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/07/you-dont-forget/#comment-29865"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-07-18T17:23:37-04:00">Monday, July 18, 2011 at 5:23 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Yes, strawberries deserve a conserve, and this one would be wonderful, I&#39;ll try it once we get strawberries again. </p>
<p>But I want to underscore your word of caution regarding the syrup &#8211; I tried to make stawberry jam last year and discovered the hard way that what you say about a &#8220;barely set syrup&#8221; is true whenever you try to make preserves with strawberries and their naturally low pectin content. But, hey, there&#39;s tons of uses for homemade strawberry syrup too!</p>
    </div>

