  <li id="comment-29877" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01446776252990520966" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Pomegranate206</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/07/you-dont-forget/#comment-29877"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-07-18T22:13:40-04:00">Monday, July 18, 2011 at 10:13 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I haven&#39;t been to the Ballard Farmers Mkt for a few weeks, so I don&#39;t know what they had yesterday. But for Molly or any other locals, perhaps you can seek out Jessie&#39;s Berries. Her berries are harvested from either from Fir Island or MV. In 2010, she sold a late variety of strawberries, and they were MUCH later than any Skagit valley strawb that I grew up with. I remember them as smaller, but were both more sweet and tart than the bigger, earlier ones.</p>
<p>The conserve recipes sounds great; but personally, I&#39;ll choose a raspberry any day. Or a local Rainier cherry, mmm&#8230;</p>
    </div>

