  <li id="comment-29897" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Susan</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/07/you-dont-forget/#comment-29897"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-07-19T16:11:48-04:00">Tuesday, July 19, 2011 at 4:11 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve had your jam making/not eating problem for years, and solve it by giving away baskets of jam at Christmas.  Best berry jam recipe I&#39;ve found (straw, black, rasp,marion, whatever) is: <br />4C Fruit<br />3C sugar (add less for super sweet berries)<br />1/4 C lemon juice<br />Let sit until juicy, and sugar is melted. Place in a WIDE pan (a stainless skillet is what I use) and cook for ten minutes.  Done. DO NOT double the recipe&#8212;make other batches.</p>
<p>I can it&#8212;but you can just put it in jars in the refrigerator.  You get pretty much what I see pictured on your post.  </p>
<p>Wild Blackberry is particularly yummy.  Especially when you&#39;ve picked the berries while wading in Lake Washington with the sun on your back.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-29897' data-commentid="29897" data-postid="565" data-belowelement="comment-29897" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Susan" aria-label='Reply to Susan'>Reply</a>    </div>
