  <li id="comment-29954" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/05777720897780837957" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Katja</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/07/you-dont-forget/#comment-29954"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-08-01T16:36:29-04:00">Monday, August 1, 2011 at 4:36 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I had just finished making strawberry jam when I sat down and saw this entry! I made 6 cups of sliced, slightly mashed strawberries, 4 tablespoons of fresh lemon juice, and 2 cups of sugar into this glorious, lazily firm jam.  The best part?  The little warm bit left over that didn&#39;t get into the jar.  We had Julie&#39;s frozen yogurt with a healthy drizzle of the strawberry stuff.  Yum!</p>
    </div>

