      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/07/you-dont-forget/#comment-30099"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-08-04T04:35:48-04:00">Thursday, August 4, 2011 at 4:35 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>imogenlily, I apologize for the slow reply!  I&#39;ve been out of town at a family wedding.  But it&#39;s wonderful that you&#39;re coming to Seattle, and to Delancey!  </p>
<p>Unfortunately, I am not the best person to ask about hotels.  (I&#39;ve never stayed in one here!)  But I&#39;ve heard good things about the Inn at the Market, the Ace Hotel, Hotel Max, and the Hotel 1000.  You might start there &#8211; and consult Tripadvisor.com, too.  I&#39;ve had good luck finding hotels that way.  As for Ballard, it is a great neighborhood for walking, yes.  Don&#39;t miss Ballard Avenue (little shops, gelato, and there&#39;s a farmers market there on Sunday mornings), and there&#39;s some good stuff on Market Street, too.  Cafe Besalu, on 24th Avenue, makes fantastic croissants and ginger biscuits.  And be sure to check out the Ballard Locks!  Delancey is a bit to the north, in a more residential area, but there is a great bakery next door and a sweet little umbrella shop&#8230;</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-30099' data-commentid="30099" data-postid="565" data-belowelement="comment-30099" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Molly" aria-label='Reply to Molly'>Reply</a>    </div>
